3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - Priority queues are commonly used in AI applications, and the paper's proposed data structure could potentially be useful in AI algorithms. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - Similar to cs.AI, priority queues are used in machine learning algorithms, and the proposed data structure could be useful in this context as well. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper involves the analysis of the time complexity of various operations on the proposed data structure, which is a topic within computational complexity.
